.TH "gfs2_rbm_from_block" 9 "gfs2_rbm_from_block" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_rbm_from_block \- Set the rbm based upon rgd and block number
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gfs2_rbm_from_block
.BI "(struct gfs2_rbm *rbm "  ","
.BI "u64 block "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rbm" 12
The rbm with rgd already set correctly
.IP "block" 12
The block number (filesystem relative)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This sets the bi and offset members of an rbm based on a
resource group and a filesystem relative block number. The
resource group must be set in the rbm on entry, the bi and
offset members will be set by this function.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or an error code
